OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1780473962
OL,3,CZero-hours contracts ban will go
OL,4,Cahead, Business Secretary tells ITV
OL,5,CNews
OL,7,FA zero-hours contract is where an
OL,8,Femployer is not obliged to guarantee a
OL,9,Fset amount of hours for staff who are
OL,10,Funder no obligation to accept shifts
OL,11,Fon offer.
OL,13,FThere are more than a million zero-
OL,14,Fhours workers in the UK, according to
OL,15,Fthe Trades Union Congress, and more
OL,16,Fthan 720,000 have worked for their
OL,17,Fcompany for over a year, but are
OL,18,Fentitled to fewer workplace rights due
OL,19,Fto the nature of their contract.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1780473962
OL,3,CZero-hours contracts ban will go
OL,4,Cahead, Business Secretary tells ITV
OL,5,CNews
OL,7,FThe business secretary said: "Most
OL,8,Femployers recognise that a workforce
OL,9,Fthat has security and predictability
OL,10,Fcan plan their lives is a more
OL,11,Fproductive one.
OL,13,F"We are bringing fairness into every
OL,14,Fworkplace, helping businesses to
OL,15,Fretain the best talent while ensuring
OL,16,Fworkers get the predictability they
OL,17,Fneed."
OL,19,FBut businesses say banning them could
OL,20,Fdiscourage hiring and, as a result,
OL,21,Fcause a rise in unemployment.
OL,26,@yD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
