OL,3,CZero-hours contracts ban will go
OL,4,Cahead, Business Secretary tells ITV
OL,5,CNews
OL,7,FThe policy to ban zero-hours contracts
OL,8,Fis part of the Employment Rights Act,
OL,9,Fwhich became law last year, but much
OL,10,Fof the detailed provisions were left
OL,11,Fblank, allowing ministers to phase in
OL,12,Fimplementation over a period of years.
OL,14,FConfirming the consultation, the
OL,15,Fbusiness secretary said: "We need to
OL,16,Fmake sure we get the implementation
OL,17,Fright, because for some people, (zero-
OL,18,Fhour contracts are) a good thing.
OL,26,@yD@apmzD@Spn
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
