PN,31708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1780473962
OL,3,CZero-hours contracts ban will go
OL,4,Cahead, Business Secretary tells ITV
OL,5,CNews
OL,7,F"Actors, for example, and students,
OL,8,Fthey want the flexibility. But the key
OL,9,Fthing is they need to be in control of
OL,10,Fthat flexibility rather than having it
OL,11,Fforced on them."
OL,13,FThe government insists workers who
OL,14,Fwant a flexibly zero-hours contract
OL,15,Fwill be allowed to "choose to have one
OL,16,Fif it suits them better. But
OL,17,Fexploitative arrangements, where
OL,18,Femployers take all the flexibility and
OL,19,Fworkers bear all the risk, will be
OL,20,Fbrought to an end."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
